{
  "_id": "fhSubEmbergrss01",
  "name": "Embergrass",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubModern00001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A loose-leaf cure of red-veined herb, rolled and smoked. Steadies the nerves and dulls the edge of a long day; chronic users complain that the days stop having edges at all.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 hour you have advantage on saving throws against being frightened, and a +1 bonus to Charisma (Persuasion) checks.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Embergrass (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Embergrass.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Intelligence checks.</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 3.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(3 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Rolling Papers.</em></p>"
    },
